cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about salient object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new method for saliency detection using an hourglass network with intermediate supervision to learn contextual features in a high-to-low manner. This involves designing a new network architecture and training strategy, which falls under the subcategories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on six different datasets, which falls under the subcategory of multimedia (cs.MM).
